The paper focuses on the process of establishing ties between two existing social networks, which falls under the category of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper mentions using efficient algorithms, which could indicate that it falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
